The account balance withdrawal benefit as at the last member reporting date.
Superannuation Contribution Account Balance Completion Date Amount
The total administration component which forms part of the super guarantee charge. The fee is for each employee that has an individual shortfall (including choice) for the assessment period.
Superannuation Contribution Administration Component Total Amount
The total choice liability amount for the quarter for all employees.
Superannuation Contribution Choice Liabilities For Quarter Total Amount
The amount of taxable component of a transitional termination payment where the member has directed the payer to make to a complying super plan or used to purchase a super annuity.
Superannuation Contribution Directed Termination Payments Taxable Amount
The number for each employee being reported in this statement, beginning with 1.
Superannuation Contribution Employee Number

The amount of Choice liability which is 25% of the notional quarterly shortfall, less any individual super guarantee shortfall for that employee for the quarter, that did not meet the choice of fund requirements.
Superannuation Contribution Employee Choice Liability Amount
Indicates whether the employer has met their choice obligations for the employee.

Valid values are:
TRUE = the employer has met their choice obligations for the employee.
FALSE = the employer has not met their choice obligations for the employee.
Superannuation Contribution Employee Choice Obligations Met Indicator
This is the Superannuation Product Identification Number (SPIN) of the employee's nominated fund. SPIN is a unique identification number issued to each Superannuation Fund in Australia.
Superannuation Contribution Employee Nominated Fund Details Superannuation Product Identification Number Number
Employee shortfall amount is the amount calculated by multiplying the employee's salary or wages by the notional quarterly shortfall percentage.
Superannuation Contribution Employee Shortfall Amount
Total number of employees reported for the quarter.
Superannuation Contribution Employees Reported For Quarter Total Number
This is the subtotal of the employee's super guarantee shortfall (excluding choice) and choice liability amounts.
Superannuation Contribution Employee Subtotal Amount
The amount of contributions made by an employer on behalf of the member.
Superannuation Contribution Employer Amount
This is the value of superannuation employer contributions recognised by the reporting party as income during the relevant period in accordance with accounting standards.
Superannuation Contribution Employer Contributions Income Amount
The total amount of Superannuation Guarantee Charge payable for an employer.
Superannuation Contribution Employer Guarantee Charge Payable Total Amount
A code for the system, describing the superannuation entity type within the administrative structure of a provider which holds the account of a member.

Valid values are:
Acting = The provider itself acting on its own behalf (the provider is self-administered) Accountancy = An accountancy practice Financial = A financial planning practice Industry = An industry administrator Liquidator = A liquidator or provisional liquidator of this provider Retail = A retail administrator Specialist = A specialist firm, consultancy or life insurance office Tax Agent = A tax agent Actuarial = An actuarial administrator Controller = A controller or administrator (as defined for the purposes of the corporations law) Trustee = The trustee of a bankrupt estate or the trustee of a deed under Part IX or Part X of the Bankruptcy Act 1966.
Superannuation Contribution Entity Type System Code
The amount of contributions made on behalf of the member by relatives, friends and third parties.
Superannuation Contribution Family And Friend Amount
The amount transferred to the provider from a foreign fund or scheme that exceeded the amount vested in the member at the time of transfer, that is included in the assessable income of the fund.
Superannuation Contribution Foreign Fund Assessable Amount
The amount transferred from a foreign fund or scheme that is not included in the assessable income of the Australian fund.
Superannuation Contribution Foreign Fund Non Assessable Amount
The total amount of Superannuation Guarantee Charge for all employees for the quarter.
Superannuation Contribution Guarantee Charge For Quarter Total Amount
The total amount of Superannuation Guarantee shortfalls (excluding choice) for the quarter for all employees.
Superannuation Contribution Guarantee Shortfalls For Quarter Total Amount
The subtotal amount of superannuation guarantee shortfalls and choice liabilities for the quarter.
Superannuation Contribution Guarantee SubTotal Amount
Indicates whether the employer wants to claim a late payment offset amount for contributions paid into the employee's fund after the cut-off date.

Valid values are:
TRUE = the employer wants to claim a late payment offset amount.
FALSE = the employer does not want to claim a late payment offset amount.
Superannuation Contribution Late Payment Claim Offset For Employee Indicator
The total late payment election amount for all employees.
Superannuation Contribution Late Payment Election Total Amount

The amount of late contributions that may be offset to reduce your super guarantee charge for the employee. This amount is limited to the sum of the nominal interest and individual shortfall (including choice liability) calculated for that same employee.
Superannuation Contribution Late Payment Offset Amount

This is the late payment election amount. The employer may elect, in the approved form, for a contribution to be offset where the contribution was made to a complying superannuation fund or Retirement Savings Account (RSA) by the employer for the benefit of an employee.
Superannuation Contribution Late Payment Offset Election Amount
The total number of employees included in the late payment offset.
Superannuation Contribution Late Payment Offset Employees Total Number
The total late payment offset amount for all employees.
Superannuation Contribution Late Payment Offset Total Amount
Indicates whether the provider will accept a co-contribution for this member.

Valid values are:
TRUE = the provider will accept a contribution for this member.
FALSE = the provider will not accept a contribution for this member.
Superannuation Contribution Member Account Accept CoContributions Indicator
The date that contributions began to be paid into, or otherwise attributed or credited to the member's account by the provider.
Superannuation Contribution Member Account Open Date
Indicates whether contributions can be accepted into the member's account.

Valid values are:
Active = the member's account is active and will accept payments from the Tax Office.
Closed = the members account is closed and will not accept payments from the Tax Office.
Superannuation Contribution Member Account Status Code

The total amount of Nominal interest which compensates the employee for the interest forfeited as a result of the employer's late payment or non-payment of their super guarantee entitlement. It is applied to the combined shortfall and choice liability components.
Superannuation Contribution Nominal Interest Component Total Amount

This is, for the duration of the relevant period, the amount of other superannuation contributions received by the reporting entity, as required to be reported on APRA form SRF_100_0.
Superannuation Contribution Other SRF 100 0 Amount
This is the description of the detailed line item comprising the other contribution revenue balancing item, as required to be reported on APRA form SRF_100_0.
Superannuation Contribution Other SRF 100 0 Description

This is the description of the detailed line item comprising the other contribution revenue balancing item, as required to be reported on APRA form SRF_200_0.
Superannuation Contribution Other SRF 200 0 Description

This is, for the duration of the relevant period, the amount of other superannuation contributions received by the reporting entity, as required to be reported on APRA form SRF_300_0.
Superannuation Contribution Other SRF 300 0 Amount
This is the description of the detailed line item comprising the other contribution revenue balancing item, as required to be reported on APRA form SRF_300_0.
Superannuation Contribution Other SRF 300 0 Description
The contributions made by a member to an account in their own name including both deducted and undeducted member contributions.
Superannuation Contribution Personal Amount
The amount of personal injury payments a member contributed before or when notifying the provider they were to be excluded from the non-concessional contribution cap.
Superannuation Contribution Personal Injury Election Amount
The amount of contributions made on or after 10 May 2006 to a non-complying fund that became a complying fund during the year.
Superannuation Contribution Previously Non Complying Fund Amount
The unique member identifier used to link member accounts within the organisation.
Superannuation Contribution Provider Client Identifier
The amount of personal contributions which a member has elected to exclude from the contributions caps because of a Capital Gains Tax (CGT) small business 15-year exemption.
Superannuation Contribution Small Business 15 Year Exemption Capital Gains Tax Election Amount

This is the amount of personal contributions which a member has elected to exclude from the non-concessional contributions cap because of a Capital Gains Tax (CGT) small business retirement exemption.
Superannuation Contribution Small Business Retirement Exemption Capital Gains Tax Election Amount
The amount of contributions made for a member by their spouse or made for a member who is a child under 18 years old.
Superannuation Contribution Spouse And Child Amount
This is the value of any Superannuation Tax plus any Superannuation Surcharge recognised in the Income (Profit and Loss) Statement by the reporting party for the relevant period.
Superannuation Contribution Tax Plus Surcharge Amount
The date the member's superannuation account was opened.
Superannuation Fund Details Account Open Date
Indicates the relationship of the supplier to the provider.

Valid values are:
Self Administered = Supplier is the provider itself (the provider is self administered).
Accountancy Practice = Supplier is an administrator of this provider and is best described as an accountancy practice.
Financial Planning Practice= Supplier is an administrator of this provider and is best described as a financial planning practice.
Industry Administrator= Supplier is an administrator of this provider and is best described as an industry administrator.
Liquidator = Supplier is a liquidator or provisional liquidator of this provider.
Retail Administrator = Supplier is an administrator of this provider and is best described as a retail administrator.
Specialist Firm = Supplier is an administrator of this provider and is best described as a specialist firm, consultancy or life office.
Tax agent = Supplier is an administrator of this provider and is best described as a tax agent.
Actuarial Administrator = Supplier is an administrator of this provider and is best described as an actuarial administrator.
Controller = Supplier is a controller or administrator of this provider (as defined for the purposes of the corporations law).
Trustee = Supplier is the trustee of a bankrupt estate or the trustee of a deed under Part IX or Part X of the Bankruptcy Act 1966.
Superannuation Fund Details Administrator Type Code
Indicates that members have been notified of the search or whether a member has provided written authorisation for a search where the entity searching is not a superannuation provider.

Valid values are:
True = members have been notified of the search or whether a member has provided written authorisation for a search where the entity searching is not a superannuation provider.
False = members have not been notified of the search.
Superannuation Fund Details Authorised Entity Indicator
The date the member finished working with the last known main employer.
Superannuation Fund Details Employment End Date
The date the member commenced working with their last known main employer.
Superannuation Fund Details Employment Start Date
This is the guarantee reference number (formerly known as voucher number) displayed on letters issued to a member advising they have contributions they can transfer to the provider of their choice.
Superannuation Fund Details Guarantee Contributions Reference Number
This is a unique account number allocated by a provider to a member's superannuation contributions.
Superannuation Fund Details Member Account Identifier
This is the balance of the member's superannuation account.
Superannuation Fund Details Member Account Balance Amount
The status of the member's account.

Valid values are:
Lost = Where the member is lost due to not being contactable with an account balance that is greater than zero.
Inactive = Where the member is lost due to inactivity with an account balance greater than zero.
Found = Where the member was previously reported as lost or inactive and has re-established contact.
Transferred = Where the member was previously reported as lost or inactive and has transferred to another super provider or the Tax Office as unclaimed monies.
Error = Where the member was previously reported in error.
Where a member is both inactive and lost, the member should be reported as 'Lost'.
Superannuation Fund Details Member Account Status Code
The date the member notified a change to their address.
Superannuation Fund Details Member Address Change Date
This is the superannuation member's client ID which assists to uniquely identify the member for the provider.
Superannuation Fund Details Member Client Identifier
Identifies where a member's date of birth has been deemed.

Valid values are:
Yes = The member's date of birth has been deemed. No = The member's date of birth has not been deemed. Unknown = It is unknown if the member's date of birth has been deemed.
Superannuation Fund Details Member Date of Birth Deemed Code
Identifies where a member's superannuation money is held.

Valid values are:
Still held = Still held by reporting provider or paid to member. Tax Office = Paid to the Tax Office as unclaimed super money. NSW = Paid to NSW as unclaimed super money. VIC = Paid to VIC as unclaimed super money. QLD= Paid to QLD as unclaimed super money. WA = Paid to WA as unclaimed super money. SA = Paid to SA as unclaimed super money. TAS= Paid to TAS as unclaimed super money. ACT = Paid to ACT as unclaimed super money. NT = Paid to NT as unclaimed super money. Transferred = Transferred to another super provider.
Superannuation Fund Details Member Money Held Code
The date that the member had a full or partial name change.
Superannuation Fund Details Member Name Change Date
Identifies the reference number reported for the member.

Valid values are:
Not supplied = Use this code where the member reference number has not been supplied. Australian Government Service (AGS) number = Use this code where the member reference number is Australian Government Service (AGS) number. Employee number = Use this code where the member reference number is the employee number. Payroll number = Use this code where the member reference number is the payroll number. Union number = Use this code where the member reference number is the union number. Other = Use this code where the member reference number is different to any of the above options.
Superannuation Fund Details Member Reference Other Code
An additional reference number for the member which is not their 'Member Account number' or 'Member Client Identifier'.
Superannuation Fund Details Member Reference Other Identifier
Indicates the reason a Non-Lodgment Advice is completed.

Valid values are:
No updates = Use this code where the provider has no lost member, and no updates to the member status of members previously reported as lost.
Transferred = Use this code where the provider has lost members not previously reported which have been transferred to another superannuation provider, and no updates to the member status of members previously reported as lost.
Nil account balances = Use this value where the provider has only lost members with nil account balances, and no updates to the status of members previously reported as lost.
Both = Use this value where the codes for both 'Transferred' and 'Nil account balances' apply. Use this value where the provider has lost members not previously reported which have been transferred to another superannuation provider, and lost members with nil account balances, and no updates to the member status of members previously reported as lost.
Superannuation Fund Details Non-Lodgment Advice Reason Code
Indicates whether notices and correspondence from the organisation are to be sent to the provider or supplier address.

Valid values are:
Provider = Notices or correspondence from the organisation are to be sent to the provider.
Supplier = Notices or correspondence from the organisation are to be sent to the supplier.
If an invalid value is present, this field will default to 'Supplier'.
Superannuation Fund Details Notice Address Code
Indicates the preferred method of receiving correspondence.

Valid values are:
Paper = Notices or correspondence should be sent to the organisation in paper format.
Electronically = Notices or correspondence should be sent to the organisation in electronic format.
Superannuation Fund Details Preferred Correspondence Method Code
This superannuation product identification number (SPIN) or product number used for identifying the product within the fund which the member account belongs to.
Superannuation Fund Details Product Identification Or Product Number Identifier
The details to identify the super provider when the 'Other' code is selected.
Superannuation Fund Details Provider Details Other Text
The provider Superannuation fund number.
Superannuation Fund Details Provider Fund Number
A reference number for the supplier that may be useful in identifying the statement if contacted for further information.
Superannuation Fund Details Supplier Reference Number
The total election amount for all employees that the employer has elected to offset against the superannuation guarantee shortfall and nominal interest.
Superannuation Payment Election For All Employees Total Amount
The late payment election amount per employee, that the employer has elected to offset against the superannuation guarantee shortfall and nominal interest for the employee.
Superannuation Payment Late Payment Election Per Employee Amount
The total amount of the late payments the employer is electing to claim for the late payment offset.
Superannuation Payment Late Payment Offset Election Total Amount

This is a balancing item in the list in which it is being used.
This is, for the duration of the relevant period, the amount of other types of lump sum benefits received by the reporting, as required to be reported on APRA form SRF_100_0.
Superannuation Payment Other SRF 100 0 Amount

This is a balancing item in the list in which it is being used.
This is, for the duration of the relevant period, the amount of other types of lump sum benefits received by the reporting, as required to be reported on APRA form SRF_200_0.
Superannuation Payment Other SRF 200 0 Amount

This is a balancing item in the list in which it is being used.
This is, for the duration of the relevant period, the amount of other types of lump sum benefits received by the reporting, as required to be reported on APRA form SRF_300_0.
Superannuation Payment Other SRF 300 0 Amount
The total number of employees that the employer has included in the Superannuation Guarantee Late Payment Offset election.
Superannuation Payment Total Employees Included In Election Number
Indicates the destination type the amount was transferred to.

Valid values are:
Roll-over = Roll-over to another provider account, including for a deferred annuity product.
Individual = Payment to an individual (pension, annuity or lump sum).
Death beneficiary = Payment to a death beneficiary (you must also have answered 'Yes' to the member deceased indicator question').
Non-member = Payment to a non-member due to marriage breakdown.
Superannuation Payment Variation Destination Code
The destination super provider's product identification number that the amount was transferred to.
Superannuation Payment Variation Destination Provider Product Identifier
Indicates the reason the provider is varying a remittance or recovery notice.

Valid values are:
Transfer = Member transfer.
Unknown = Member account unknown to provider.
Member Account = Member account cannot accept super co-contribution, SG allocation, SHA special account allocation, or Government FHSA contribution from the Tax Office.
Insufficient = Insufficient Contributions.
Trust Deed = Trust deed/governing rule does not permit recovery from member account.
No TFN = No TFN held for the member.
If the account has been transferred to another provider, individual or to the member, as a full transfer, use code 'Transfer'.
Superannuation Payment Variation Reason Code
Identifies the destination super provider when contributions have been transferred from a member's account.
Superannuation Payment Variation Reference Transfer Out Information Identifier
The credit or debit request amount for the member as shown on the remittance or recovery notice.
Superannuation Payment Variation Rejected Amount
The reference number shown on the remittance or recovery notice issued by the Tax Office.
Superannuation Payment Variation Tax Office Reference Number
